---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Uses - Jeremiah Church"
  description="Hardware, software, and tools I actually use, maintained honestly."
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-2">Uses</h1>
  <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-10 max-w-[60ch]">
    The stuff I actually reach for. Updated when things change, not when things are
    trendy.
  </p>

  <div class="space-y-10 max-w-[60ch]">
    <section>
      <h2 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-3">
        Daily driver
      </h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-[16px]">
        <li>Windows + WSL for most work</li>
        <li>Claude is my hallucinating bestie</li>
        <li>VS Code or IntelliJ, depending on the day</li>
        <li>1Password for everything that needs a secret</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-3">
        Stack
      </h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-[16px]">
        <li>Ruby on Rails, Node, and just enough Go to be dangerous</li>
        <li>Postgres, Redis, and NATS</li>
        <li>Cloudflare for DNS, edge, and static hosting</li>
        <li>Tailscale for every ops tunnel I would otherwise regret</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-3">
        Shop &amp; lab
      </h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-[16px]">
        <li>A Hyundai Wia mill-turn for the real work</li>
        <li>
          A Cincinnati Milacron 3-axis that runs Windows NT 3.5 and is old enough to
          vote. I overclocked it anyway.
        </li>
        <li>64 kW of rooftop solar backed by 136 kWh of lithium</li>
        <li>CT clamps on every branch circuit, because I want to know</li>
        <li>Home Assistant + ESPHome running the whole thing</li>
        <li>Too many oscilloscopes for any single person</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-3">
        On the road
      </h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-[16px]">
        <li>An RV that is slowly being re-engineered from the inside out</li>
        <li>One very good dog</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
